overview.text_en:
In the morning, head to the Palace of Versailles located in the southwestern suburbs of Paris, and tour the Palace of Versailles;
In the afternoon, head to visit Notre-Dame de Paris and the Île de la Cité, then visit the Champ de Mars and the Eiffel Tower (exterior) by the Seine. Take a Seine River cruise to tour Les Invalides (exterior), the Grand and Petit Palais (exterior), the Musée d'Orsay (exterior), and other places, touring the central Paris attractions all day.
Overnight: Mercure Paris or Novotel, or an equivalent 4-star hotel

On the morning of the day, gather in downtown Reykjavik and travel to Keflavik Airport to assemble; you may then proceed to the Blue Lagoon hot spring scenic area (Blue Lagoon) and choose to enjoy a Blue Lagoon hot spring ticket package; or take the coach to Reykjavik and choose a midday whale-watching trip out to sea; in the afternoon, after passing Keflavik Airport, head to Reykjavik. Overnight at the Reykjavik Grandi Central Hotel or an equivalent four-star hotel.
Itinerary arrangement for the day:
1. Gathering time and place: 09:00 downtown Reykjavik (recommended to choose either the Blue Lagoon hot spring or whale watching);
2. Gathering time and place: 09:45 Keflavik Airport (recommended to choose either the Blue Lagoon hot spring or whale watching);
3. Gathering time and place: 16:00 downtown Reykjavik (Blue Lagoon hot spring cannot be chosen);
4. Gathering time and place: 16:45 Keflavik Airport (Blue Lagoon hot spring cannot be chosen).
Depending on the different departure dates, the order of sightseeing may vary, but all sightseeing content is identical and does not affect the overall experience; it is regarded as the same route for the departure date, and the specific time order is subject to the "Departure Notice".
Because the Blue Lagoon hot spring is located in a remote area and the visit takes a relatively long time, if you do not enter the Blue Lagoon hot spring, no sightseeing or rest can be arranged around the Blue Lagoon scenic area.

In the morning, visit the Louvre Museum, the pride of France, where a curator from the French national museum will give an in-depth thematic tour on selected highlights;
In the afternoon, head to Notre-Dame de Paris, the Île de la Cité, the Eiffel Tower (exterior) and the Champ de Mars, then take a Seine River cruise to view Les Invalides (exterior), the Grand and Petit Palais (exterior), Place de la Concorde and other sights, spending the whole day touring the landmarks of central Paris.
Overnight: Mercure Hotel Paris or Novotel Hotel or an equivalent 4-star hotel

In the morning, visit the Louvre Museum, the pride of France, where a guide from the French national gallery will provide an in-depth thematic commentary on carefully selected topics;
In the afternoon, go to visit Notre-Dame de Paris, Île de la Cité, the Eiffel Tower (exterior) and the Champ de Mars, then take a Seine River cruise to view Les Invalides (exterior), the Grand and Petit Palais (exterior), Place de la Concorde and other sites, touring the attractions in the center of Paris for the whole day.
Overnight: Mercure Paris Hotel or Novotel Hotel or an equivalent 4-star hotel

In the morning, go to the fashion center of Paris, Boulevard Haussmann and Rue Royale, and freely visit the fashion districts such as the Paris Opera (exterior), Printemps department store and Galeries Lafayette in Paris;
In the afternoon, head to the Palace of Versailles located in the southwestern suburbs of Paris and tour the Palace of Versailles; then return to the hotel.
Overnight: Mercure Paris Hotel or Novotel Hotel or an equivalent 4-star hotel

